text.section:
The Department shall serve children in the juvenile services system with programming that:
ensures the safety of the community and the children served;
holds delinquent children accountable to victims and communities;
assists children to develop competencies to become successful members of society;
delivers services on a regional basis through at least four operational regions;
ensures that each committed facility owned by the Department serves no more than 48 children at one time; and
ensures that each committed facility licensed by the Department serves no more than 48 children at one time, unless the Secretary finds good cause for a committed facility licensed by the Department to serve more than 48 children at one time; and
uses detention and committed facilities that are operationally separate from each other and that do not share common program space, including dining halls and educational or recreational facilities.
